Text description: A claim can be approved, after it has been created.
The approval of the claim should be preceded by the creation of the claim.
A claim should be approved before it can be paid out.
If a surgery is performed, then prescription of rehabilitation occurs eventually after it.
If a request is sent, then a proposal is expected to be prepared afterwards.
Every provided room service must be billed.
Sending an invoice is required to create a claim.
The creation of a claim is required after sending an invoice.
Creating a claim must precede sending an invoice.
A car must be inspected before it can be sold.
If a flight is booked, the ticket should be issued.
An event must be planned before it can be executed.
Upon receiving a package, it must be logged into inventory.
Following article writing, it should be subject to editorial review.

The successful execution and hosting of an event or gathering necessitate meticulous and strategic event planning and coordination efforts upfront, encompassing logistical arrangements, resource allocation, scheduling, and attendee management, ensuring a seamless and memorable experience for all participants and attendees involved.
Before a recipe is prepared, the ingredients must be gathered.
A presentation can only be delivered after the slides are prepared.
If a customer submits a support ticket, they should receive a response within 24 hours.
Designing a website comes before coding its functionality.

Before starting the webinar, the presentation slides need to be uploaded to the platform right before.

Prior to the event kickoff, the banners and decorations must be hung up right before.

Once the order is confirmed, processing the payment should be immediate.
The conclusion of the day entails reflection on accomplishments.
Logging in is the first action required.
Locking the door should be the final action.
At the outset, setting up the equipment is mandatory.
As a starting point, turning on the lights is necessary.
As the final task in the project, presenting findings is essential.
To complete the transaction, confirming payment is necessary.
Every project begins with outlining the objectives.
To initiate the review process, uploading the document is necessary.
The process kicks off with a detailed project kickoff meeting.
The process is terminated after all outstanding issues are resolved.
A system reboot should be performed sparingly and may occur at most once to resolve technical issues.
Rolling back database changes should be avoided except in emergencies and may occur at most once.
Reviewing and updating company policies must occur at least once a year to ensure compliance with regulations.
Attending at least one networking event is essential.
Taking extended breaks during work hours is tolerated, but it should not happen more than once a day.
Throughout her studies, Sarah must have attended at least one guest lecture per semester to gain diverse insights.
Throughout his career, John has to mentor at least one junior colleague to pass on his knowledge and experience.
Inspections must be conducted at least once.
Assignments must be completed at least once.
Appointments must be confirmed at least once.
A cancellation request cannot be made more than once.
The deployment of new software updates should preclude the rollback to previous versions, and vice-versa.
The start of a print job and the cancellation of a print job are mutually exclusive tasks.
Gardening in the backyard and playing video games should never occur together.

Biking in the park and skateboarding on the sidewalk should never occur together.

Completing online training should not occur together with attending in-person workshops.

Completing a physics lab should not occur together with attending a chemistry lecture.
Signing up for Module A should preclude signing up for Module B, and vice versa.
Completing the coursework for Module A should preclude dropping Module B, and vice versa.
The selection of Module A topic and Module B topic should not coexist within the research project.
